        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="556" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                <head>Peterborough Improvement Commissioners</head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Peterborough</placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-02">May 2, 1865</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>The Improvement Commissioners of the city of Peterboro’, in the county of
                        Northampton, Old England, being the local authority of the city, at their
                        meeting held on the 2d day of May, 1865, unanimously passed the following
                        resolution:</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Resolved</hi>, That this meeting desires to express its
                        grief and horror at the cruel assassination of President Lincoln, and the
                        murderous attack upon Mr. Seward, and to convey to Mrs. Lincoln and the
                        United States government an expression of profound sympathy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Signed on behalf of the meeting:</salute>
                    <signed>W. STRONG, </signed>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chairman</hi>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
